description:
The would-be hijinks of the mischievous Matsuno sextuplets are hijacked from episode one by colorful buck-toothed con man Iyami and Chibita, his bald munchkin sidekick. Nearly every episode is a standalone comedy cavalcade with the above cast as well as other quirky locals who show up in a number of different roles as the series shifts effortlessly between time periods and genres, but in most cases, Iyami and Chibita are front and center as partners in crime, a couple of sad sacks scraping by but carrying out scammy schemes in order to get rich quick.

(Source: Discotek Media)

node.description: Shigehiro Suzuki is a producer and an animation producer.

Affiliated with [Studio Pierrot](https://anilist.co/studio/1/).

Noted for his work on Pierrot's long-runners in the '80s and '90s, such as the shoujo shows [Mahou no Yousei Persia](https://anilist.co/anime/2039/), [Mahou no Star Magical Emi](https://anilist.co/anime/2038/) and [Anmitsu-hime](https://anilist.co/anime/6093/), as well as the second [Osomatsu-kun](https://anilist.co/anime/9883/) and [Heisei Tensai Bakabon](https://anilist.co/anime/19961/).

Close friends with [Shinsaku Kouzuma](https://anilist.co/staff/135006/) and [Masahito Yamashita](https://anilist.co/staff/138566/).
**Fujio Akatsuka** was a pioneer Japanese artist of comical manga known as the "Gag Manga King".

Yuuji Nunokawa was a planner, producer, as well as the founder and representative director of [Studio Pierrot](https://anilist.co/studio/1/).

Worked at [Tatsunoko Production](https://anilist.co/studio/103/) as an animator and director through the '70s before becoming a producer.

[Wiki (jp)](https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/水野和則)

Freelancer with strong ties to [Studio Pierrot](https://anilist.co/studio/1/) at the time of his passing.

Passed away while sleeping at his desk at Pierrot.

Affiliated with [Studio Pierrot](https://anilist.co/studio/1/).

He was Planner, Production Manager and an Anime Producer for Studio Pierrot since the 90s. 

He's the Representative Director of [Studio Signpost](https://anilist.co/studio/6109/).

[Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/shichiro_kobayashi/)

A former art director and a guest professor at Kobe Design University.

Kobayashi graduated from Musashino Art University and first became an elementary school art teacher. It was only later that he joined the animation industry in 1964. He started quickly making a name for himself as a background artist and consequently established his own background art studio Kobayashi Production, in 1968. During this time thick poster paint was dominating the backgrounds in anime, but Kobayashi started a new style with much thinner painting and colored pencil strokes.

He has worked as an art director on over 100 titles and is one of the most distinguished art directors in the medium. Notable works include [Gamba no Bouken](https://anilist.co/anime/5267/), [Ie Naki Ko](https://anilist.co/anime/2828/), [Takarajima](https://anilist.co/anime/2618/), [Tenshi no Tamago](https://anilist.co/anime/885/), [Utena](https://anilist.co/anime/440/), [Berserk](https://anilist.co/anime/33/) and [Nodame Cantabile](https://anilist.co/anime/1698/).

Kobayashi retired from the industry in 2010, which was followed by his studio's closedown a year later.

In a 2015 [interview](https://youtu.be/V1tiKOsCz2M), Kobayashi talked about his life and passion in painting touring his atelier and showcasing his work.
Akira Shigino is an anime director. He's a member of JAniCA.
Yumiko Shigeoka is a producer working for Fuji TV.
